data.title: St. Peter Parish: Welcome to St. Peter Parish
data.text:
is to celebrate that we are a diverse people who

grow in faith,

work together in hope,

worship together in love,

bear one another's sorrows,

forgive one another's faults,

share one another's joys,

we will see with the eye of the heart,

look for God in one another,

and see God in everyone.

We are a welcoming Catholic community called by God to live out the message of Christ in love and service to all people.

Stay up-to-date with the latest news, events, and spiritual resources from our Parish community.

2024 Annual Catholic Appeal

The 2024 Annual Catholic Appeal is underway in Western Washington! This annual fundraising campaign supports vital ministries, programs, and services throughout our region, including Catholic schools, pastoral care, community outreach, and more. Your generous contributions make a significant difference in fostering faith, supporting those in need, and building a stronger Catholic community.

Join us in supporting this important initiative and making a positive impact on the lives of many.

Support St. Peter Parish

Red Apple Donates to St. Peter - Do you shop at Red Apple? If so, please consider placing your receipts in the Red Apple receipt box located at the front entryway of the church. Red Apple generously donates to our church based upon eligible purchases. Receipts must be submitted intact without modifications and should be submitted as soon as possible. Receipts dated last year are ineligible and are discarded. Red Apple receipts is an easy way for you to support our church every time you shop at no cost to you. If you have any questions, please see Ana Juguilon. Thank you.

If the parish office is closed and you need a priest to administer the Sacrament of the Sick, please call the emergency number at 206-420-2079 Call: 206-769-5611. If the priest does not answer, please leave a message and he will call you back.

THIS NUMBER IS FOR EMERGENCIES ONLY.

And Jesus came and said to them, "All authority in heaven and on earth has been given to me. Go therefore and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, teaching them to observe all that I have commanded you; and lo, I am with you always, to the close of the age."
